## Giddy for GitOps?

[GitOps](/topics/gitops/) takes DevOps best practices that are used for application development such as [version control](/topics/version-control/), collaboration, compliance, and CI/CD, and applies them to infrastructure automation.

GitLab is the [DevOps platform](/topics/devops/) that does it all, and it’s built using Git, making it the ideal solution for GitOps processes.

First, we explained [how GitLab and Ansible can be used together for GitOps](/blog/2019/07/01/using-ansible-and-gitlab-as-infrastructure-for-code/) processes and [infrastructure as code](/topics/gitops/infrastructure-as-code/). In a follow-up post, we explain how [GitLab can also be paired with Terraform for GitOps](/topics/gitops/gitlab-enables-infrastructure-as-code/) and IaC.

