## Visibility

One of our principles at GitLab is to [dogfood everything](/handbook/engineering/development/principles#dogfooding), so you can rest assured that we aren’t about to introduce an engineering feature without first trying it out for ourselves. When it comes to our Insights tool though, the process happened in reverse. Our Engineering Productivity team at GitLab needed a particular tool, and as we built it, we realized it would benefit our GitLab Ultimate customers. Read on to [learn how our Insights tool came to be](/blog/2020/01/30/insights/).

Dig into this [valuable explanation of how we discovered that Prometheus query language can be used to detect anomalies](/blog/2019/07/23/anomaly-detection-using-prometheus/) in the time-series data that GitLab.com reports.

